comments: Olynyk (UTA) moves alongside Harris' (PHI) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Tucker (PHI) and Olynyk (UTA) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Thybulle (PHI) moves alongside Clarkson's (UTA) path as marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Markkanen (UTA) moves alongside Maxey's (PHI) path as incidental contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Replay review of the out of bounds called on Harris (PHI) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Olynyk (UTA) touches the ball last before going out of bounds.
Clarkson (UTA) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Embiid (PHI) briefly clasps and releases Markkanen's (UTA) arm off ball as they engage and disengage for position and the contact is marginal.
Tucker (PHI) goes to, not through, Olynyk's (UTA) space and marginal contact occurs as the two come together during the screen.
Maxey (PHI) and Olynyk (UTA) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs as the pick is set.
Thybulle (PHI) clamps and holds Markkanen's (UTA) left arm, which affects his ability to pursue the rebound.
Maxey (PHI) maintains a legal pivot foot after he gathers the ball.
Thybulle (PHI) initiates contact with Olynyk's (UTA) arm that affects his SQBR.
Tucker (PHI) enters the lane during the release of the free throw.

Tucker (PHI) initiates illegal contact with Markkanen (UTA) as he attempts to get to the pass. After communicating with the Replay Center, it is determined that the foul occurred after the throw-in was released.
Conley (UTA) commits a take foul on Embiid (PHI). The transition take foul rule doesn't apply to the last two minutes of the fourth quarter or overtime.
Milton (PHI) maintains a legal guarding position as Clarkson (UTA) moves into him during his jump shot.
